'''Zhu Hongzhao''' (朱弘昭) (d. May 14, 934<ref name=ZZTJ279>''[[Zizhi Tongjian]]'', [[:zh:s:資治通鑑/卷279|vol. 279]].</ref>) was a general of the [[History of China|Chinese]] [[Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period]] state [[Later Tang Dynasty]]. He was a close associate of its second emperor [[Li Siyuan]], and became particularly powerful during the short reign of Li Siyuan's son and successor [[Li Conghou]] while serving as chief of staff (樞密使, ''Shumishi''). Traditionally, he and fellow chief of staff [[Feng Yun (Later Tang)|Feng Yun]] were blamed for making inappropriate sensitive personnel movements that caused Li Conghou's adoptive brother [[Li Congke]] to be fearful and rebel, eventually leading to Li Conghou's being overthrown and Zhu's own death.

[[Thailand]] | homepage = [http://www.syndicate.asia www.syndicate.asia] }} '''Syndicate Legal''' is a full service commercial [[law firm]] operating in [[Southeast Asia]] from its head office in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]. The firm was founded by David Washenfelder (formerly a partner of [[Baker & McKenzie]]). Syndicate's typical clients range from large publicly listed [[Fortune Global 500]] corporations, closely held businesses, and investment funds. The formation of Syndicate brought together a scalable platform of local legal talent and seasoned US professionals with a long history of practicing in [[Asia]], to service business clients seeking Asia’s growth and opportunity. Syndicate is incorporated in [[Hong Kong]] and [[Thailand]]. The firm has professional experience advising cross-border transactions and direct investments in [[Hong Kong]], [[Singapore]], [[Thailand]], [[Vietnam]], [[Cambodia]], [[Laos]], [[Indonesia]], [[Burma]] and [[Malaysia]]. [http://www.syndicate.asia www.syndicate.asia] [[File:1 hongkong panorama victoria peak 2011.JPG|thumb|Hong Kong]] [[File:All Seasons Plaza Bangkok.jpg|thumb|All Seasons Place, Bangkok]] ==Asia== Syndicate Legal focuses on [[Asia]], currently the fastest growing world region.{{cite web|title=Asia will remain the world's fastest-growing region|url=http://gfs.eiu.com/Article.aspx?articleType=rf&articleId=1877744372&secId=1|publisher=The Economist Intelligence Unit|accessdate=19 July 2011|language=English|month=January|year=2011}} The firm is headquartered in what is widely considered the hub of [[Southeast Asia]]. High growth coupled with [[economic development]] means the nations of [[Southeast Asia]] are particularly important contributors to Asia’s growth{{cite web|title=Migration and Growth in East and South-East Asia|url=https://www.gtap.agecon.purdue.edu/resources/download/5219.pdf|author=Terrie Walmsley, Angel Aguiar, and S. Amer Ahmed}} and in fact several key [[ASEAN]] economies will grow faster than the rest of [[Asia]] over the next five years.{{cite web|title=Capturing the investment-banking opportunity in ASEAN|url=http://www.mckinsey.com.tr/fikirler/mckinsey_quarterly/capturing-the-investment-banking-opportunity-in-asean.view|publisher=McKinsey Quarterly|month=January|year=2011}} Among the forces propelling [[Southeast Asia]] forward are investments in [[infrastructure]], the expansion of the member nations’ [[capital markets]], outbound [[investment]]{{cite web|title=Capturing the investment-banking opportunity in ASEAN|url=http://www.mckinsey.com.tr/fikirler/mckinsey_quarterly/capturing-the-investment-banking-opportunity-in-asean.view|publisher=McKinsey Quarterly|month=January|year=2011}}, and local demand for more sophisticated products and services. Rising mass consumption and the increasing global demand for made-in-Asia products will continue to provide a favorable investment environment. The regional aspect of Synidcate's practice recognizes the geography-specific needs of clients as well as the importance of local [[regulatory]] issues. ==Industry expertise== *[[Venture Capital]] *[[Energy]] & [[Natural Resources]] *[[Hotels]] & [[Resorts]] *[[Media & Entertainment]] *[[Information Technology]] *[[Manufacturing]] *[[Insurance]] *[[Transportation]] & [[Logistics]] ==Practice areas== *[[Mergers & Acquisitions]] *[[Foreign Direct Investment]] *[[Joint Ventures]] *[[Corporate]] & [[Commercial]] *[[Property Development]] *[[Employment]] *[[Supply]] & [[Distribution]] *[[Compliance]] *[[Dispute Resolution]] ==Recent notable engagements== ==Founders== ===David Washenfelder=== David Washenfelder is a US qualified [[attorney]] who has practiced in [[Asia]] since year 2000 as a legal advisor to [[Fortune Global 500]] companies in [[corporate]] and [[commercial]] matters, with particular focus on [[mergers and acquisitions]], [[foreign direct investment]], and [[compliance]]. His industry focus is [[venture capital]], [[energy]] and [[natural resources]], hotels and resorts, and [[media]]. Prior to co-founding Syndicate Legal, he was a partner with the global law firm [[Baker & McKenzie]]. Early in his career he practiced commercial [[litigation]] and corporate [[bankruptcy]] [[law]] with Fisher & McGuire in [[Houston]], [[Texas]]. Mr. Washenfelder served on the Board of Governors of the [[American Chamber of Commerce]] in [[Thailand]] for four years, and served concurrently as vice-president for two years. He was elected vice-chairman of the Joint Foreign Chambers of Commerce Legal Committee in 2010, and served on the Thailand Board of Trade[http://www.thaichamber.org], Competition Committee from 2008 to 2010. Washenfelder has been a contributing author to several publications on the topic of [[mergers and acquisitions]] and [[foreign direct investment]], including ''Merger Control Worldwide'', published by Cambridge University Press.{{cite web|title=Merger Control Worldwide|url=http://www.cambridge.org/aus/catalogue/catalogue.asp?isbn=9780521857888|publisher=Cambridge University Press}} He has been singled out for his [[mergers and acquisitions]], and [[real estate]] and [[construction]] work by Asia Pacific Legal 500[http://www.legal500.com]. ==References== {{Reflist}} [[Category:Law firms]] [[Category:Law firms in Asia]]

Forced into a well-timed "vacation" he never asked for Josh finds himself in Bangkok with a price on his head, a morally ambiguous brother who is knee deep into the Thai mafia, and a propensity for getting shot at. Unfortunately for Josh, the only way out is to give up information he doesn't know he has.

==Devcoin==
Devcoin is an ethically inspired project based on the BitCoin crypto-currency and created to help fund open source projects created by writers and software developers. For a quick overview, there is a [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xE4whwzRmQ0 an animated introduction to devcoin].
Participants in the DevCoin economy earn DevCoins in proportion to their project development. Writers earn devcoins by writing, Developers earn devcoins by developing, Marketers earn devcoins by Marketing, and Administrators earn devcoins by applying their time and effort to help organize the DevCoin project.
Hopefully devcoin will eventually fund all types of developers including hardware developers, graphic artists, musicians, and filmmakers.
==Purpose== The purpose of the devcoin is to give money to open source developers for their work in as fair a manner as possible.
Many open source developers do not get a significant amount of money for their work. Advertising, charity and sometimes consulting provide some income, but many developers, even those with projects used by several thousand people, only get a few dollars a month. In a typical economy, in the ballpark of 1% goes to charity. That is not enough to support people.
Because developers get so little, they can only develop their projects in their spare time, which makes development really slow. Feature requests and critiques do not accelerate development, money will.
Devcoins provide an income for everyone who wants to work, even if they live in an area with more job seekers than jobs. With devcoin, no one who wants to work need be completely out of money. Anyone who does good work will get some devcoins. There is no guarantee that this will be a high income, but something is way better than nothing.
By buying devcoins you help developers and give the world more open source software, books, music, art, and movies.
==Motto== From the many, one
From one, the source
==Mining== Devcoin is merged mined with bitcoin. There are at least two pools which merge mine devcoins along with bitcoins.
If you are mining devcoins as a secondary chain, you will get devcoin blocks much more often than bitcoin blocks, because the devcoin hash rate is much lower than the bitcoin hash rate. The mining portion of the devcoin block is 5,000 devcoins.

The {{nihongo|'''''Lycée Seijo d'Alsace'''''|アルザス成城学園|''Aruzasu Seijō Gakuen''}} was a Japanese boarding high school in [[Kientzheim]], [[Haut-Rhin]],<ref>[http://web.archive.org/web/20050403134615/http://perso.calixo.net/~lycee-seijo/ Home page]" ([http://archive.is/SieQv Archive]).''Lycée Seijo''. Retrieved on 2 January 2014. "8, route d'Ammerschwihr, 68240 KIENTZHEIM, FRANCE"</ref> in the [[Alsace]] region of [[France]], near [[Colmar]].<ref name=Seijoclose>"[http://archive.is/JkMA Seijo Gakuen closes French campus]." ''[[The Japan Times]]''. Sunday February 13, 2005. Retrieved on 2 January 2013.</ref> It was affiliated with [[Seijo University]].
The school opened in April 1986.<ref name=Seijoclose/> In 1990 it had 200 students.<ref name=Lalsace>"[http://www.lalsace.fr/actualite/2013/03/19/du-lycee-seijo-au-centre-d-etudes-japonaises Du lycée Seijo au Centre d’études japonaises]." ([http://www.webcitation.org/6MLDvM2U5 Archive]) ''[[L'Alsace]]''. 19 March 2013. Retrieved on 2 January 2014. "L’ancien lycée Seijo, à Kientzheim, a accueilli des élèves japonais entre les années 1980 et 2006. On y trouve aujourd’hui le Centre européen d’études japonaises." and "Le lycée Seijo a compté jusqu’à 200 élèves vers 1990. Il a fermé ses portes en 2006, suite au déclin progressif de la présence nippone."</ref> During the school's lifetime, some students were from [[Japanese community in Paris|Japanese families living in Paris]].<ref name=ConteHelmp85>Conte-Helm, Marie. ''The Japanese and Europe: Economic and Cultural Encounters'' (Bloomsbury Academic Collections). [[A&C Black]], December 17, 2013. ISBN 1780939809, 9781780939803., p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=DKwVAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA81 85].</ref> The school's enrollment declined due to a declining Japanese birthrate and a decreased economic presence of Japanese companies in France, due to the recession in Japan. On Friday February 11, 2005 the school held its final graduation ceremony, with 13 students graduating. In the school's history a total of 556 students had graduated.<ref name=Seijoclose/> The ''Centre européen d’études japonaises'' opened at the site of the former school.<ref name=Lalsace/>
==Notable students== * The eldest son of [[Tsutomu Hata]], who was one of the first to graduate from this school<ref name=Seijoclose/>
==See also== * ''[[Institut Culturel Franco-Japonais – École Japonaise de Paris]]'', Japanese school near Paris * [[Keio Academy of New York]] (Japanese boarding high school in the United States) * ''[[Lycée Konan]]'' - Defunct Japanese boarding school near Tours * [[Tennessee Meiji Gakuin High School]] (defunct Japanese boarding school in the United States)

Summary of Remote Control Grab
Remote control grab is a new type of handling tools with the marine crane for loading and unloading bulk cargo. It doesn’t need any additional power. There is a battery inside the grab, the battery only supplies the power for solenoid valve. so Remote Control Grab is an environmentally tool.
Working Principle
Put the grab on the cargo, when the crane lifts up, the grab will close by itself. When pressing the emitter, the receiver will receive the signal and the solenoid valve will get power. The grab will open automatically. Put the grab on the cargo again, it will enter into next cycle.
Advantage of Remote Control Grab
1.There are few hydraulic and electrical parts, it is cheaper.
2.The hydraulic and electric control parts use the plug-in modular design, easily maintain and repair, suitable for ship ocean voyages.
3.When the crane lifts up, the grab can close together with hook. It doesn’t need any additional power.
4.The grab can open in the air, it has high efficiency.
5.The grab can stop opening in any time.
6.Energy conservation, the battery has long working time.

{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} '''Henry Jordan''' (19 November 1818 – 30 June 1890) was a dentist and member of the [[Legislative Assembly of Queensland]], Secretary for Public Lands 1887 to 1888.<ref name=adb> {{Australian Dictionary of Biography |first=A. A. |last=Morrison |title=Jordan, Henry (1818–1890) |id2=jordan-henry-3871 |accessdate=3 January 2014 }}</ref>
Jordan was born in [[Lincoln, England|Lincoln]], [[Lincolnshire]], England, the son of John Jordan, a Wesleyan minister from Devonshire stock, and his wife Elizabeth, ''née'' Jefferies.<ref name=adb/>
Jordan was educated by his father, entered Kingsford College, Bristol,<ref name=adb/> and then studied at London Institution for Diseases of the Teeth.<ref name=Mennell>{{cite Australasia|Jordan, Henry}}</ref> Jordan built up a lucrative dental practice in Derby. He published ''Practical observations on the Teeth'' (London, 1851) which ran to two editions and was highly praised in England and America; it later won him election to the Odontological Society of Great Britain.<ref name=adb/>
In February 1856 Jordan arrived in [[Queensland]], and was a member of the first Board of Education in Queensland, and represented the [[Electoral district of Town of Brisbane|Town of Brisbane]] in the first session of the first Parliament.<ref name=Mennell/> From January 1861 to December 1866 he was in London as Commissioner and [[Agent-General]] for Immigration,<ref name=Mennell/> and from 23 December 1868 to 20 October 1871 he sat in the Assembly as member for [[Electoral district of East Moreton (Queensland)|East Moreton]].<ref name=parl> {{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.qld.gov.au/apps/formermembers/memberBio1.aspx?m_id=170 |title=Jordan, Henry |work=Former Members |publisher=Parliament of Brisbane }}</ref> In 1875 he was appointed Registrar-General, which office he held until 1883. He was elected to the Assembly for [[Electoral district of South Brisbane|South Brisbane]] on 21 August 1883.<ref name=parl/> In August 1887 he succeeded [[Charles Dutton (politician)|Charles Dutton]] as Secretary for Public Lands, and went out of office with his colleagues in June 1888. At the general election on 12 May 1888 he was re-elected for South Brisbane. He died on 30 June 1890 at his home, Sherwood, survived by his wife, four sons and three daughters (four other children predeceased him).<ref name=adb/>

==Gameplay==
XSquare is a puzzle game inspired by pentominos. But it mixes polyomino from 1-block monomino to 5-block pentomino that fit at most 5x5 box.
=== Game Modes === ==== Travel ==== In the first "Travel" mode player has to pass the levels with different degree of difficulty one by one. There are 7 degrees of difficulties. Every level can be played again without time limits.
==== Death ==== In the second "Death" mode, player has to pass as many levels as he can at a time. If you failed in one level, you lose the whole game. Each level is generated randomly. You can almost never meet a duplicate level.
=== Music Scores === XSquare features original music from a talented music studio- GameSound.

{{Japanese name|Yamashita}} {{nihongo|'''Tokuo Yamashita'''|山下徳夫|Yamashita Tokuo|October 7, 1919 - January 1, 2014}} was a Japanese politician.
== Life == Born in [[Imari, Saga|Imari]], and a graduate of Fukuoka Middle School (present-day [[Fukuoka Prefectural Fukuoka High School]]), he studied law first at [[Meiji University]] and then at [[Senshu University]], graduating in 1944.
After honing his skills as a politician in the Saga Prefectural Assembly (where he eventually became [[Speaker (politics)|speaker]]), he was elected to the [[House of Representatives]] in [[Japanese general election, 1969|1969]] on a ticket from the [[Liberal Democratic Party (Japan)|Liberal Democratic Party]]. After that, he won reelection ten times in a row. In [[Yasuhiro Nakasone]]'s second cabinet, he was named Transport minister. In Nakasone's third cabinet he was to lead the Management and Coordination Agency.
In [[Toshiki Kaifu]]'s first cabinet he was named [[Chief Cabinet Secretary]], but had to resign after only 16 days due to a sex scandal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1310&dat=19890825&id=U_RVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=l-EDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5775,6097412|title=Sex scandal forces out key official|publisher=The Register Guard, Eugene, Oregon|accessdate=January 3, 2014}}</ref>
In [[Kiichi Miyazawa]]'s cabinet he was [[Minister of Health, Labour, and Welfare]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jiji.com/jc/c?g=obt_30&k=2014010200072|title=山下徳夫氏死去＝元官房長官|publisher=[[Jiji Press]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=January 3, 2014}}</ref>
Between 1988 and 2003 he was chairperson of the board of trustees of his alma mater, Senshu University.
He retired from national politics in 2000, but remained an adviser for the Saga branch of the LDP.
He died in Imari on January 1, 2014 of old age.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.47news.jp/CN/201401/CN2014010101001227.html|title= 山下徳夫元厚相が死去国鉄民営化に尽力|publisher=[[Kyodo]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=January 3, 2014}}</ref>

'''Eric Striker''' is a [[linebacker]] for the [[Oklahoma Sooners football]] team. In 2013 he was a sophomore. He wears #19 and is 6' tall. He grew up in [[Seffner, Florida]] and attended [[Armwood High School]], where he set the record for career sacks with 42. He had had 125 tackles and 16 sacks as a junior in high school.<ref>[http://www.soonersports.com/ViewArticle.dbml?ATCLID=208409651 Eric Striker biography] Oklahoma Sooner</ref>
==College career== As a sophomore, Striker played on the team that won the [[Sugar Bowl]] over Alabama. Striker sacked Alabama's quarterback, picked up the fumble, and ran it in for a touchdown to seal Oklahoma's victory in the Sugar Bowl.The Sooners team also won the Big 12 Championship over [[Oklahoma State]]. Earlier in the season, he flipped Texas' quarterback [[Case McCoy]] in the game against the [[Texas Longhorns]]; he was penalized for hitting him high on the play.<ref>[http://bleacherreport.com/articles/1808497-oklahoma-lb-eric-striker-flips-texas-qb-case-mccoy-with-monster-hit]</ref> An [[Oklahoma State University]] [[cheerleader]] tried to trip him after Striker scored the final touchdown in Oklahoma’s 33-24 win over OSU.<ref>[http://fansided.com/2013/12/10/oklahoma-state-cheerleader-facing-punishment-attempting-trip-eric-striker/]</ref>
==High School Career= Striker was highly recruited.

{{Infobox person | name = Morgan Carpenter | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1966 | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Australian | residence = | education = | other_names = | occupation = Community activist | known_for = Intersex activist, president of [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]] | television = | website = {{URL|oii.org.au}} }}
'''Morgan Carpenter''' is an [[intersex]] activist and researcher who became president of [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]] in September 2013. Australia's ''Gay News Network'' included him in their "LGBTI people to watch in 2014".<ref name="watch-2014">[http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/feature/lgbti-people-to-watch-in-2014-12633.html LGBTI people to watch in 2014], Gay News Network, 1 January 2014.</ref>
== Activism ==
Morgan Carpenter helped found [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]] in 2009 and became president of the organisation on 1 September 2013, on the retirement of [[Gina Wilson]]. Carpenter was previously the organisation's secretary.<ref name="changes">[http://www.starobserver.com.au/news/changes-at-oii-as-trailblazer-gina-wilson-retires/109176 Changes At OII As Trailblazer Gina Wilson Retires ], [[Star Observer]], 13 September 2013</ref><ref>[http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/news/board-changes-at-oii-australia-gina-wilson-steps-down-11841.html Board changes at OII Australia: Gina Wilson steps down], Gay News Network, 2 September 2013</ref><ref name="oiiboard">[http://oii.org.au/information/board/, The OII Australia Board], Organisation Intersex International Australia, 12 October 2013.</ref> Carpenter has played an important role in making the organisation's case to a Senate committee inquiry on ''Involuntary or coerced sterilisation of intersex people in Australia'', and securing the inclusion of 'intersex status' in anti-discrimination legislation.
=== Anti-discrimination legislation ===
Writing in [[The Guardian]], Morgan Carpenter described intersex as a biological issue: "Intersex people have queer bodies. We disprove a binary worldview. Some of us also have queer identities, reflecting our embodiment. This is why intersex is a separate attribute in the sex discrimination amendment. It's not a matter of sexual orientation or gender identity – we have just as diverse sexualities and gender identities as everyone else."<ref>[http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/jun/18/intersex-people-australia Australia can lead the way for intersex people], Morgan Carpenter in [[The Guardian]], 18 June 2013</ref> Carpenter wrote OII Australia's submissions to Senate inquiries and appeared before a Senate hearing.<ref name="oiiboard" /><ref>[http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/news/board-changes-at-oii-australia-gina-wilson-steps-down-11841.html Board changes at OII Australia: Gina Wilson steps down], Gay News Network, 2 September 2013</ref>
A [[Senate of Australia]] inquiry into anti-discriminination legislation supported the approach of [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]] and "intersex status" was added to the ''Sex Discrimination Amendment (Sexual Orientation, Gender Identity and Intersex Status) Act 2013'', which passed into law on 1 August 2013.<ref>[http://oii.org.au/21774/welcome-senate-inquiry-anti-discrimination/ We welcome the Senate Inquiry report on the Exposure Draft of the Human Rights and Anti-Discrimination Bill 2012], [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]], 21 February 2013</ref><ref>[http://oii.org.au/22713/sex-discrimination-amendment-intersex-status-act/ On the historic passing of the ''Sex Discrimination Amendment (Sexual Orientation, Gender Identity and Intersex Status) Act 2013''], [[Organisation Intersex International Australia]], 25 June 2013</ref><ref>[http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/feature/a-watershed-moment-11346.html A Watershed Moment], Gay News Network, 2 July 2013.</ref>
=== Bodily autonomy ===
In submissions to a Senate committee inquiry on involuntary or coerced sterilisation, Carpenter has called for "normalising" surgeries on intersex infants to end, saying that such interventions "erase" traits intersex from society.<ref>[http://www.starobserver.com.au/news/forced-intersex-surgery-genital-mutilation/106957 Forced intersex surgery ‘genital mutilation’], Star Observer, 24 July 2013.</ref> He has criticised "psychosocial" rationales for surgery that include "reduced opportunities for marriage or intimate relationships” and reduced “capacity to earn an income", stigmatisation and "risk of social isolation”.<ref>[http://www.starobserver.com.au/opinion/column-intersex-rights-the-next-fight/111543 COLUMN – Intersex rights: the next fight], [[Star Observer]], 25 October 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.lgbtihealth.org.au/sites/default/files/LGBTIHealthUpdate-MAY2013.pdf LGBTI Health Update, Vol. 3, No. 4, May 2013], National LGBTI Health Alliance, May 2013</ref><ref>[http://oii.org.au/22160/intersex-health-hid2013-plenary/ Intersex health – Morgan Carpenter's presentation to Health in Difference conference], OII Australia, 22 April 2013</ref><ref>[http://oii.org.au/22995/its-time-to-stop-cosmetic-genital-surgery-on-intersex-infants/ It's time to stop cosmetic genital surgery on intersex infants], OII Australia, 18 July 2013</ref><ref>[http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/news/senate-inquiry-reveals-forced-surgery-on-intersex-children-11467.html Senate Inquiry reveals forced surgery on intersex children], Gay News Network, 25 September 2013.</ref>
Writing at the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]'s [[The Drum (TV program)|The Drum]], Morgan Carpenter, the president of OII Australia wrote, "The Senate Committee has changed the debate on the correct treatment of intersex differences. If adopted, its recommendations will effectively protect the rights of intersex children and future adults."<ref name="drum">[http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-11-15/carpenter-its-time-to-defend-intersex-rights/5093966 It's time to defend intersex rights], Morgan Carpenter at [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]], [[The Drum (TV program)|The Drum]], 15 November 2013</ref> Those recommendations include national guidelines developed with community input, and legal scrutiny of clinical decisions<ref>[http://gaynewsnetwork.com.au/news/intersex-advocates-address-findings-of-senate-committee-into-involuntary-sterilisation-12237.html Intersex advocates address findings of Senate Committee into involuntary sterilisation], Gay News Network, 28 October 2013.</ref>
While opposing use of "[[Disorders of Sex Development]]" or "DSD", as "pathologising" terminology,<ref>[http://oii.org.au/23387/august-submission-senate-inquiry-sterilisation/ Concluding submission to the Senate Inquiry on involuntary or coerced sterilisation], OII Australia, 12 September 2013.</ref> Carpenter is named as a reviewer for a "DSD Genetics" website funded by the [[National Health and Medical Research Council]] Australia.<ref>[http://dsdgenetics.org/index.php?id=20 DSD Genetics], Disorders of Sex Development Research Website, 9 October 2013</ref>
=== Identification documents ===
Following the recognition of non-binary gender identities in Australian regulations, and German "third sex" birth certificates, Carpenter has expressed concern that such developments are "not a solution to the needs of intersex infants", saying that "normalising surgeries" remain the "most fundamental concern".<ref>[http://www.dw.de/third-sex-option-on-birth-certificates/a-17193869 Third sex option on birth certificates], [[Deutsche Welle]], 1 November 2013.</ref><ref name="rt" /><ref>[http://www.starobserver.com.au/news/intersex-activist-questions-german-law-reform/112143 Intersex activist questions German law reform], Star Observer, 8 November 2013.</ref> "It’s important to recognise that intersex is not synonymous with gender diversity,” Carpenter explains. “Many intersex people are men or women and it’s crucial not to coerce them into a third option. It’s also important to avoid using infants and children as the means to pursue rights and liberties for adults."<ref name="watch-2014" /><ref>[http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/act-government-bill-will-introduce-wider-gender-identification-20131128-2yejc.html ACT government bill will introduce wider gender identification], Lisa Cox in [[Canberra Times]], 28 November 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gSxTyQ8lWMy9por7A-KorL8oJheA?docId=CNG.6aedec13aac3d301f17ad4715b7f43f1.171 Australia embraces new gender guidelines], [[Agence France-Presse]], June 14, 2013.</ref> Nevertheless, as the recipient of a passport with an 'X' sex descriptor, Carpenter says that travel to the United States is impossible with that passport,<ref name="rt">[http://rt.com/news/germany-allows-third-gender-062/ ‘X’ gender: Germans no longer have to classify their kids as male or female], [[RT (TV network)|RT]], 3 November 2013.</ref> and that both "same sex marriage" and "opposite sex marriage" exclude some intersex people, who "would need to seek and obtain a new birth certificate to be eligible to marry their partners – certification that reflects governments’ demands, not individual liberty or biology."<ref>[http://www.starobserver.com.au/news/day-to-celebrate-and-build-awareness-of-intersex-lives/111381 Day to celebrate and build awareness of intersex lives], Star Observer, 23 October 2013.</ref>

'''Marie Knights''', known by her stage name '''Fe''' is an independent British singer-songwriter.
==Music career==
===2013-present: ''Let It Go'' and worldwide success=== Fe uploaded her first track, "Let It Go", on [[YouTube]] on February 20th, 2013.<ref>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DBsMG834JyU</ref> She also uploaded the song on [[Soundcloud]], and gained much success, thousands of views and different music blogs shared the song. Two months later, Fe uploaded a second song, "Remarkable Affair". She was compared with [[United States|american]] singer [[Lana Del Rey]].<ref>http://pigeonsandplanes.com/2013/04/is-fe-the-next-lana-del-rey/</ref> Fe uploaded to her [[Facebook]] page some snippets of new songs. Onh October 4th, 2013, she released two new tracks on Soundcloud, "Mother Russia" and "Giddy Up", calling the attention of both the media and fans.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/FEKNIGHTS/posts/632976283392015</ref>
On October 23rd, 2013, Fe released a preview of her new video and single.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/FEKNIGHTS/posts/642653445757632</ref> About releasing an EP in the future, she said that she "has no limits" and she's "plotting 2014".<ref>https://www.facebook.com/FEKNIGHTS/posts/642657999090510</ref><ref>https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=659049307451379&set=a.156033681086280.29541.132271773462471&type=1</ref> On December 31st, 2013, she confirmed via Facebook that she's releasing new music in 2014. <ref>https://www.facebook.com/FEKNIGHTS/posts/676048159084827</ref>
"Let It Go" was played on [[Le Grand Journal]] in June 2013 and it was one of the most played tracks on [[Music Week]]. The song "Giddy Up" is part of the [[Mercedes Benz]]' mixed tape on [[Spotify]].<ref>https://play.spotify.com/track/7piSvN56iVVhTQ1DwqfJ0z?play=true&utm_source=open.spotify.com&utm_medium=open</ref>
==Artistry== ===Voice and music=== Fe is [[mezzo-soprano]]. Her voice, music and image was compared with Lana Del Rey. Lots of music blogs called Fe a "new version" of the famous indie pop singer. Fe mixes different genres such as indie pop, [[dream pop]] and [[chamber pop]]. She also has some [[trip hop]] influences.
===Influences=== Although she never gave an interview, Fe said she loves the american [[indie rock]] band [[The National (band)|The National]].<ref>https://www.facebook.com/FEKNIGHTS/posts/664021276954182</ref> She also likes [[Coldplay]] and [[Scala & Kolacny Brothers]].<ref>https://www.facebook.com/FEKNIGHTS/posts/571599106196400</ref>

revision.text: David C. Burnham was born in 1974, in the town of Gloucester, Massachusetts. Being the youngest child in a large family, he strived to find his niche. Early in his youth, David Burnham began experimenting with genetic mutations of several Herptiles. At the age of 14 he began the daily management of his Family's locally owned Pet Shop. It was not long after being handed over the management that he turned this small pet shop into a status for Herp collectors, throughout the New England Area. At age 16, David Burnham had moved to the Hyannis, Massachusetts area, and opened a new branch to the family businesses Pet Shop. He was featured in numerous Pet Trade and Area print for his unique and info oriented approach to the introduction of Herptiles to the masses. It was during this time that David Burnham helped progress the New England Herp Society through his local Pet Shop. David Burnham wrote numerous care sheets and care guides to help facilitate the proper care of Reptiles and Amphibians. With the help of fellow Herpetologist Kevin McCurly of NERD, David Burnham began introducing a growing number of exotic specimens to the average consumer. In 1994, David Burnham became one of only few people that successfully bred Olive Pythons and D'Alberts Pythons in Captivity. With the expertise of Kevin McCurly and the New England Herp Society, he was able to help introduce captive bred specimens to the general public.

200 watts night| erp = | haat = | branding = | slogan = | class = | former_callsigns = WKKD, WFVR| webcast = | website = | callsign_meaning = '''W'''ill, '''K'''ane, '''K'''endall and '''D'''uPage| sister_stations = | }} '''WKKD''' 1580 [[AM broadcasting|AM]] was a [[radio station]] licensed to [[Aurora, Illinois]]. The station began broadcasting in 1960 and initially ran 250 watts during daytime hours only with a directional pattern towards Aurora.Ghrist, John R. "Valley Voices: A Radio History" 1996. (p. 106) The station began simulcasting on 95.9 [[WERV-FM|WKKD-FM]] in 1961. The stations initially aired a [[Full service (radio format)|full service]] format that focused heavily on [[Country music]],[http://books.google.com/books?id=CiEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA8&dq=WKKD+Aurora&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=1#v=onepage&q=WKKD%20Aurora&f=false Folk Talent & Tunes] Sachs, Bill. (p. 8) Billboard. July 10, 1961. Accessed January 2, 2014[http://books.google.com/books?id=fR8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA38&dq=WKKD+Aurora&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=5#v=onepage&q=WKKD%20Aurora&f=false Folk Talent & Tunes] Sachs, Bill. (p. 38) Billboard. July 18, 1960. Accessed January 2, 2014[http://books.google.com/books?id=uB8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA47&dq=WKKD+Aurora&lr=&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=13#v=onepage&q=WKKD%20Aurora&f=false Folk Talent & Tunes] Sachs, Bill. (p. 47) Billboard. May 16, 1960. Accessed January 2, 2014[http://books.google.com/books?id=ew8EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA50&dq=WKKD+Aurora&as_pt=MAGAZINES&cd=6#v=onepage&q=WKKD%20Aurora&f=false Nashville Scene] Whisenhunt, Elton. (p. 50) Billboard. February 5, 1966. Accessed January 2, 2014 By the early 1970s the simulcast had ended with WKKD-FM adopting a [[Beautiful music]] format. AM 1580's callsign was changed to WFVR, and it continued to air the country music format. WFVR's format was later changed to [[Adult Contemporary]]-[[Middle of the road (music)|MOR]].[http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Station-Albums/Chicago-Trib-1979-Mar-About-Chi-Radio.pdf Stations, everywhere: a listeners' guide to the AM and FM bands] ''Chicago Tribune Magazine''. March 4, 1979. Accessed January 2, 2014 In the early 1980s the station's callsign was changed back to WKKD and it again simulcast WKKD-FM. In the mid '80s the station began broadcasting during nightime hours. By the late 80s the simulcast had ended, and WKKD AM had begun airing an [[oldies]] format.[http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Other-Documments/Chicago_Magazine/Chicago-1989-Fall.pdf WKKD AM 1580] Radio Chicago. Fall 1989. (p. 18) Accessed January 2, 2014[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1990-02-25/features/9001170010_1_beasley-broadcast-group-format-big-band-station Radio In Du Page] Wilhelmson, Brenda. ''Chicago Tribune.'' February 25, 1990. Accessed January 2, 2014 In the early 1990s WKKD-FM began simulcasting the oldies format of WKKD AM, and the stations became known as "Pure Gold 96"[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1993-02-12/entertainment/9303180714_1_irish-rovers-concert-pure-gold Lettermen Bring Valentine Spirit To Norris] Todorovich, Lisa. ''Chicago Tribune.'' February 12, 1993. Accessed January 2, 2014 In March 1995, 1580 left the simulcast and began airing the [[Real Country]] [[country music]] format.[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1995-03-26/features/9503260089_1_fm-oldies-station-music-director-and-assistant Reporters Have New Assignments On Ch. 2 Mission] Nidetz, Steve. ''Chicago Tribune''. March 26, 1995. Accessed January 2, 2014 On July 1, 1996, the station adopted a [[Spanish language]] [[Tejano music]] format as "Viva 1580".[http://web.archive.org/web/19970414123243/http://www.wkkd.com/new.htm What's New @ WKKD Salter Broadcasting] wkkd.com. April 14, 1997. Internet Archive. October 10, 1997. December 18, 2007. ''Quad City Business Journal''. February 25, 2008.
